Art, regarding your latest post: Huh?<br><br>
You got me. I guess I better break out my new age crystal and contemplate my cosmic dust mites, cause I don't get what you said, at all.  I didn't know I diagnosed anyone and my reference to &quot;most psychologists not knowing much about PTSD&quot; or the like, is sadly true.  I know alot about it, I have helped treat it, done well too, but I have never walked in the shoes, or combat boots, on anyone who had it, so I can only be a voyeur at best, as all shrinks really are.<br><br>
Tom, Sorry but I just can't find the sympathy or compassion that you have. I respect that you do, but I have been accosted too many times, at too many corners, by every form of low-life, crack smoking, cardboard carrying, bum, then I care to remember.  Downtown Los Angeles is a blight, with crowds of BUMS  (remember that word, our parents used to use it, along with HOBO'S)  at every corner.  And if you don't dig up a buck, you get flipped off or spit at more times than not.  Maybe that is just L.A., but nobody paid my way through life, and a job is good for the soul.  In particular are the &quot;will work for food&quot; guys. Offer them a sandwich and they cuss you out. Two sandwiches for an hour of gardening and they think you are crazy.  Compassion for this, sorry,<br>
I gave at the office.
